{humble} rosidl-generator-py: Explicitly set Python target

Python 3.12+ started to be strict about separate of the embeddeing
vs extension APIs. This means that the Python3::Python target
must be explicitly added in order to ensure that necessary
symbols be found at link time.

This problem doesn't appear directly in rosidl-generator-py builds
but when building packages like builtin-interfaces that use
the tool themselves.

Upstream-Status: Inappropriate [oe specific]

Signed-off-by: Rob Woolley <rob.woolley@windriver.com>

Index: rosidl-generator-py-0.14.6-1/cmake/rosidl_generator_py_generate_interfaces.cmake
===================================================================
--- rosidl-generator-py-0.14.6-1.orig/cmake/rosidl_generator_py_generate_interfaces.cmake
+++ rosidl-generator-py-0.14.6-1/cmake/rosidl_generator_py_generate_interfaces.cmake
@@ -191,7 +191,7 @@ target_include_directories(${_target_nam
   ${CMAKE_CURRENT_BINARY_DIR}/rosidl_generator_py
 )
 
-target_link_libraries(${_target_name_lib} PRIVATE Python3::NumPy Python3::Module)
+target_link_libraries(${_target_name_lib} PRIVATE Python3::NumPy Python3::Module Python3::Python)
 
 rosidl_get_typesupport_target(c_typesupport_target "${rosidl_generate_interfaces_TARGET}" "rosidl_typesupport_c")
 target_link_libraries(${_target_name_lib} PRIVATE ${c_typesupport_target})
@@ -233,6 +233,7 @@ foreach(_typesupport_impl ${_typesupport
     ${_target_name_lib}
     ${rosidl_generate_interfaces_TARGET}__${_typesupport_impl}
     Python3::Module
+    Python3::Python
   )
 
   target_include_directories(${_target_name}
